connect

public TrackerWebServicesClient connect(java.lang.String systemId,
                                        java.lang.String systemKind,
                                        java.lang.String repositoryId,
                                        java.lang.String repositoryKind,
                                        java.lang.String connectionInfo,
                                        java.lang.String credentialInfo,
                                        boolean forceResync)
                                 throws MaxConnectionsReachedException,
                                        ConnectionException
Connects to the source CEE system using the connectionInfo and credentialInfo details. This method uses the ConnectionManager configured in the wiring file for the CEEReader

Parameters:
systemId - - The system id of the source CEE system
systemKind - - The system kind of the source CEE system
repositoryId - - The tracker id in the source CEE system
repositoryKind - - The repository kind for the tracker
connectionInfo - - The CEE server URL
credentialInfo - - User name and password concatenated with a delimiter.
forceResync - true if initial resync after artifact creation should be enforced
Returns:
- The connection object obtained from the ConnectionManager
Throws:
MaxConnectionsReachedException
ConnectionException

setResyncUserName

public void setResyncUserName(java.lang.String resyncUserName)
Sets the optional resync username The resync user name is used to login into the CEE instance whenever an artifact should be created. This user has to differ from the ordinary user used to log in in order to force initial resyncs with the source system once a new artifact has been created.

Parameters:
resyncUserName - the resyncUserName to set
